[{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_1","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":1,"text":"When I have healed Israel, then shall the iniquity of Ephraim be revealed, and the wickedness of Samaria; for they have wrought falsehood: and a thief shall come in to him, a robber spoiling in his way;","searchKeywords":["when","have","healed","israel","then","shall","the","iniquity","ephraim","revealed","and","wickedness","samaria","for","they","wrought","falsehood","thief","come","him","robber","spoiling","his","way"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_2","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":2,"text":"that they may concert together as singing in their heart: I remember all their wickedness: now have their own counsels compassed them about; they came before my face.","searchKeywords":["that","they","may","concert","together","singing","their","heart","remember","all","wickedness","now","have","own","counsels","compassed","them","about","came","before","face"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_3","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":3,"text":"They gladdened kings with their wickedness, and princes with their lies.","searchKeywords":["they","gladdened","kings","with","their","wickedness","and","princes","lies"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_4","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":4,"text":"They are all adulterers, as an oven glowing with flame for hot-baking, on account of the kneading of the dough, until it is leavened.","searchKeywords":["they","are","all","adulterers","oven","glowing","with","flame","for","hot","baking","account","the","kneading","dough","until","leavened"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_5","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":5,"text":"the days of our kings, the princes began to be inflamed with wine: he stretched out his hand with pestilent fellows.","searchKeywords":["the","days","our","kings","princes","began","inflamed","with","wine","stretched","out","his","hand","pestilent","fellows"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_6","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":6,"text":"Wherefore their hearts are inflamed as an oven, while they rage all the night: Ephraim is satisfied with sleep; the morning is come; he is burnt up as a flame of fire.","searchKeywords":["wherefore","their","hearts","are","inflamed","oven","while","they","rage","all","the","night","ephraim","satisfied","with","sleep","morning","come","burnt","flame","fire"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_7","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":7,"text":"They are all heated like an oven, and have devoured their judges: all their kings are fallen; there was not among them one that called on me.","searchKeywords":["they","are","all","heated","like","oven","and","have","devoured","their","judges","kings","fallen","there","was","not","among","them","one","that","called"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_8","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":8,"text":"Ephraim is mixed among his people; Ephraim became a cake not turned.","searchKeywords":["ephraim","mixed","among","his","people","became","cake","not","turned"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_9","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":9,"text":"Strangers devoured his strength, and he knew not; and grey hairs came upon him, and he knew not.","searchKeywords":["strangers","devoured","his","strength","and","knew","not","grey","hairs","came","upon","him"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_10","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":10,"text":"And the pride of Israel shall be brought down before his face: yet they have not returned to the Lord their God, neither have they diligently sought him for all this.","searchKeywords":["and","the","pride","israel","shall","brought","down","before","his","face","yet","they","have","not","returned","lord","their","god","neither","diligently","sought","him","for","all","this"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_11","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":11,"text":"And Ephraim was as a silly dove, not having a heart: he called to Egypt, and they went to the Assyrians.","searchKeywords":["and","ephraim","was","silly","dove","not","having","heart","called","egypt","they","went","the","assyrians"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_12","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":12,"text":"Whenever they shall go, I will cast my net upon them; I will bring them down as the birds of the sky, I will chasten them with the rumour of their affliction.","searchKeywords":["whenever","they","shall","will","cast","net","upon","them","bring","down","the","birds","sky","chasten","with","rumour","their","affliction"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_13","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":13,"text":"Woe to them! for they have started aside from me: they are cowards; for they have sinned against me: yet I redeemed them, but they spoke falsehoods against me.","searchKeywords":["woe","them","for","they","have","started","aside","from","are","cowards","sinned","against","yet","redeemed","but","spoke","falsehoods"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_14","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":14,"text":"And their hearts did not cry to me, but they howled on their beds: they pined for oil and wine.","searchKeywords":["and","their","hearts","did","not","cry","but","they","howled","beds","pined","for","oil","wine"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_15","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":15,"text":"They were instructed by me, and I strengthened their arms; and they devised evils against me.","searchKeywords":["they","were","instructed","and","strengthened","their","arms","devised","evils","against"]},{"verseId":"brenton_hosea_7_16","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":33,"bookName":"Hosea","bookAbbrev":"hosea","chapter":7,"verse":16,"text":"They turned aside to that which is not, they became as a bent bow: their princes shall fall by the sword, by reason of the unbridled state of their tongue: this is their setting at nought in the land of Egypt.","searchKeywords":["they","turned","aside","that","which","not","became","bent","bow","their","princes","shall","fall","the","sword","reason","unbridled","state","tongue","this","setting","nought","land","egypt"]}]